`String` (conflicting-types)

  `String` is a `String` or a `Number`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `String` must be the same type as `_` and `Number`; double-check these.

  1. `filter`: `filter` is a `((String or Number) -> Boolean) -> (Box (String or Number)) -> Sequence (String or Number)`. This requires `As-Sequence` `(Box (String or Number))` `(String or Number)`.

  2. `_`: `_` is annotated with the type `Box String`.

  3. `positive?`: `positive?` is `(_ :: Number) -> _`. This means `(_ :: Number) -> _`, `positive?`, and `positive?` must be a `(String or Number) -> Boolean`.

  (2 -> 1)


